First Lady Melania Trump recently visited the Republic of Korea to support the United States Embassy's "Girls Play 2!" campaign, which promotes the 2018 Winter Olympics and encourages girls' participation in sports. She also attended a welcoming ceremony at the Blue House and participated in tea and a friendship walk with President Moon and Mrs. Kim. Mrs. Trump and Mrs. Kim attended a joint press conference held by their husbands and ended the day with a state banquet. On her second day, Mrs. Trump thanked employees and families at the U.S. Embassy for their service and accompanied her husband to a speech at the National Assembly. They also took part in a wreath laying ceremony at the National Cemetery before concluding the visit with a departure ceremony at Osan Air Base. Mrs. Trump expressed her gratitude for the warm welcome and looks forward to continuing the friendship and supporting the people of the Republic of Korea.